                " \n \nASSOCIATE PROFESSOR \nDepartment: Performing Arts\nPost Level: 6\nRef: 23/259\nThe Department of Performing Arts in the Faculty of Arts and Design has a permanent position for an Associate Professor at the Arts Campus.\n \nCore functions:\nThe successful candidate will be responsible for the following:\nTeaching undergraduate courses, supervising postgraduate, Master\u2019s and Doctoral candidates.\nParticipating in students\u2019 projects, departmental productions, and Work Integrated Learning (WIL), academic administration, community engagement activities. \nCapturing and processing marks and other administrative tasks relating to teaching and learning activities.\nContributing actively to the research and publication profile of the department.\nDeveloping learning material aligned to undergraduate and postgraduate programs based on the new curriculum.  \n \nRequirements\nA doctorate degree NQF level 10 in the fields of Performing Arts (Dance, Music, Theatre Arts and Design).\nBe a seasoned academic researcher.\nHold professional skills in Performing Arts.\nAbility to collaborate with relevant stakeholders in the Performing Arts industry.\n \nExperience\nExtensive experience in teaching at tertiary institutional level (a minimum of 10 years).\nProven record of supervision of Masters\u2019 and Doctoral students.\nProven track record of research publications in accredited journals. \nEvidence of attendance at local and international conferences.\nMembership or active involvement in national and/or international boards, societies, councils, etc. in the field of performing arts.",
